  "description": "<i>Zgadula</i> is a game loosely based on the TV game show named Wheel of Fortune. The players take turns guessing the consonants or buying the vowels to form a word or a saying. The game allows to play up to three human or computer players for on up to nine rounds. Each turn begins with the wheel spin, determining a win prize for the consonant or ending up with bankruptcy or loss of the turn. After the last round a winner is the player with the largest amount of money.",
